definition: many/much/often/a lot of/numerous/more/in excess/how (to what extent)/multi-/Taiwan pr. [duo2] when it means "how"
next in sequence/second/the second (day, time etc)/secondary/vice-/sub-/infra-/inferior quality/substandard/order/sequence/hypo- (chemistry)/classifier for enumerated events: time

sentences.english: Even in time of danger, many times in body armor.
sentences.chinese: 甚至在危险时刻，多次以身相护。

sentences.english: We have disputed about this issue many times.
sentences.chinese: 我们已经针对这个议题吵过好多次了。

sentences.english: If women are clean water, the ones who have fallen in love time after time are footbath water.
sentences.chinese: 如果说女人是水，那么恋爱多次的女人就象洗脚水。

sentences.english: Peformances are many times on everyday.
sentences.chinese: 唱圣歌的表演每天都有很多次。

sentences.english: She has made so many passes at me recently that I think it necessary to freeze her off.
sentences.chinese: 最近她多次向我抛送秋波，我觉得有必要疏远她。

sentences.english: Many times a coward before death, death of terror.
sentences.chinese: 懦夫在未死之前，已身历多次死亡的恐怖了。

sentences.english: You two treated me many times before when I was looking for a job. Now I’m making good money, so it should be my turn.
sentences.chinese: 以前我在找工作的时候，你们两请我吃过好多次饭。

sentences.english: The textology of the Qing Dynasty is an old subject in the academic circle.
sentences.chinese: 清代考据学是学术界多次探讨的老问题。

sentences.english: Talk to her more and you will find that she isn't 70 bad 71 you thought she was.
sentences.chinese: 和她谈过多次你就会发现她不像你原来认为的那么坏。

sentences.english: China and Africa have long-lasting political instability, several mutinies and coups.
sentences.chinese: 中非政局曾长期持续动荡，多次发生兵变和政变。

sentences.english: Cumulate probability distribution of trials of random variable of uniform distribution.
sentences.chinese: 随机变数多次试验结果之累积机率为均匀分布。

sentences.english: It has been held irregularly since 1995.
Wang Bingnan was sent to take part in several meetings held by Gung Ho in its initial period.
sentences.chinese: 王炳南被派去参加了工合早期的多次会议。

sentences.english: Over the years, North Korea has made many attacks near the island.
sentences.chinese: 多年以来，北韩多次向延坪岛附近发动袭击。

sentences.english: Stretch your toes up and down several times.
sentences.chinese: 多次上下舒展你的脚趾。

sentences.english: As to the China-UK relations, we have made our position clear to the UK.
sentences.chinese: 关于中英关系，我们已多次向英方表明立场。
